The issue is that the pom.xml didn't get updated with JUnit 5 dependencies. The test file is trying to use JUnit 5, but the pom.xml is still using JUnit 4.

Let me push the correct pom.xml with JUnit 5:Perfect! ✅ **pom.xml has been successfully updated!**

**The issue was:** You need **both** JUnit Jupiter dependencies:
1. `junit-jupiter-api` (contains the annotations like `@Test`)
2. `junit-jupiter-engine` (the runtime engine to execute tests)

**Changes made:**
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.junit.jupiter</groupId>
    <artifactId>junit-jupiter-api</artifactId>
    <version>5.9.3</version>
    <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.junit.jupiter</groupId>
    <artifactId>junit-jupiter-engine</artifactId>
    <version>5.9.3</version>
    <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>
```

Your build should now pass! The compiler will find the `org.junit.jupiter.api` package and all test annotations. 🚀
